[ 645768 ] kernel dropping packages
    [enhancement/bugfix]
    - Packets are being dropped by the kernel before being written to the
      link layer on some machines. You can confirm that by running a
      parallel tcpdump. After you finish it with Ctrl+C:

      26392 packets received by filter
      24156 packets dropped by kernel

      These packets never hit the target. In my machine the dropping started
      after about 240 packages have been sent.

      Tested on machines running Conectiva Linux snapshot (kernel 2.4.19). I
      believe it's some configuration from /proc or from the kernel
      compilation options.

